                    <h2>Mission Statement</h2>
                    <p>
                        Broward Professional League (BPL) is an adult, non-profit soccer league created to provide a platform for traditional
                         and intermediate soccer players to exercise and improve their fitness level. 
                        It is an after work/school program designed to keep the community healthy.
                         On this vein, one can understand that playing soccer is another way to do sport and stay healthy, as sometimes one may not have the motivation to go to the gym.
                         The advantage of doing sport is priceless.
                         And in almost every medical malaise, if not all, exercising is a way to control, retard or even prevent the attack of illnesses, as diabetes,
                         high blood pressure, heart disease, and depression, to name a few. The league provides just this medium. If you are 18 years old or older,
                         males and females, this league is your league of choice. 
                        The qualifying participants may come from all walk of life that includes the school based employees, students,
                         medical professionals, lawyers, friends, families, or anyone who meets the criteria the league advocates.
                         BPL will be sensitive to foster an environment of peace, violence free/tranquility and friendly to make soccer/sport a fun venue for all.
                    </p>

                    <br />
                    <h2></h2>
                    <p>
                        
                    </p>
                   
