                    <h2>Tournaments</h2>
                    The league organizes two (2) tournaments a year, Fall and Spring season, plays a total of ten (10) regular games per season and a post-season for six (6) teams with the best record.
                    Rained game delayed is to be postponed. The coordinator, in concertation with the City of Plantation, is responsible to reschedule the non-played games at the end of the regular season. 
                    <hr>

                    <h2>Games time</h2>
                    The games are to be played every Sunday at 6:15 PM and 8:00 PM on Pine Island Park (320 S. Pine Island RD., 
                    Plantation, FL. 33324), or Central Park, in Plantation (9151 NW 2nd Street, Plantation, FL. 33324)
                    <hr>

                    <h2>Fee of participation</h2>
                    The fee of participation is $ 55.00. We try to keep the fee low to allow almost everyone to be part
                    of this family of soccer and at the same times to be able to cover the expenses.
                    <hr>

                    <h2>Uniform</h2>
                    The league will provide a jersey respective to the team at the beginning of Fall Tournament,
                    and a pair of socks in spring season. The player is responsible for a black short pants, shin-guards, and cleats.
                    <hr>

